@node INTRODUCTION "Introduction"
---<Introduction to KewlCaller>---

  KewlCaller is a MAXsBBS Door that reads the Caller Log and displays the 
  last ten (or as many as there are if less than ten) callers to the BBS.

  This door was inspired by "FCaller" - a door by M.Recardo, however it
  is different in that there is only one executable and doesn't need to
  execute any extra programs at log-off :-) and unlike FCaller, KewlCaller
  works out the time on-line correctly!!

  Now features configuration - the Sysop can now choose how many callers 
  to display, plus, what information is shown.


   


@{"< >" Link MAIN} Return to the Main Menu
@endnode
@node INSTALLATION "Installation"
---<Installing KewlCaller>---

  Simply Unarchive the KewlCaller Archive to your DOORS: Path. This is
  done by using one of the Amiga's standard Archivers...

      CLI> C:LhA x KewlCaller_15.lha DOORS:

  The Archive will automatically create the `KewlCaller' Directory within
  your BBS Doors Directory.

  Now, To use KewlCaller, You will need any version of the `MAXsBBS'
  BBS System. This can be obtained from Aminet or from any decent BBS!

  You can either setup this Door as a MAXs Menu item or as a Logon Door
  using the `IntroDoor.Text' or `MainDoor.Text' files.

  -<MAXsBBS Menu Item>-

  Now, Simply load up your copy of MAXsBBS Professional, and go to the
  `Menu Editor' Window...

  Locate the Menu in which you want to use the KewlCaller Door....

  Change the Menus to read...
  in MaxsBBS 1.54 :-

  Key  Function  Extra  Lo Acc  Hi Acc  Path/Filename/Extra...
    ?        34      0       ?       ?  DOORS:KewlCaller/KewlCaller

  or in MaxsPro :-
    ?        34      0       ?       ?  DOORS:KewlCaller/KewlCaller + 

  The `Key', `Lo Acc' and `Hi Acc' figures can be whatever you wish as
  these figures are upto the SysOp of the BBS.

  Please, DO NOT FORGET to add the `+' (Plus) sign at the End of the
  `Path/Filename/Extra...' Gadget as this tells KewlCaller that you are
  using MAXsBBS Professional.

  -<Door Scripts>-

  Load any of the Door Scripts `IntroDoor.Text', `MainDoor.Text',
  and add the following line to wherever you want KewlCaller to be 
  launched from...

  KewlCaller/KewlCaller

  or

  KewlCaller/KewlCaller +     (For MaxsPro)

  Now, Save the Door Script...


@{"< >" Link MAIN} Return to the Main Menu
@endnode
@node CONFIGURATION "Configuration"
---<Configuring KewlCaller>---

Right then, here we go - this is new so listen carefully! ;-)

In "Doors:Kewlcaller" you will need a file called KewlCaller.cfg:-

  Line 1 - How many callers to display
  Line 2 - Indent from the left of the screen to the table of info
  Line 3 - No. of fields to display

 The following lines refer to the displayed fields; they are dealt with
 in two lines ... the first line is the field-name and the second is
 the colour of the text.

 i.e.

  Line 4 - NAME
  Line 5 - 1

 This equates to The Caller's name displayed as white text :)

Okay here are the possible fields

 NAME - 20 chars - Caller's name
 DATE -  8 chars - Date they logged on
 TIME -  5 chars - Time they logged on
 USED -  4 chars - Time they were online
 BAUD -  6 chars - Baud rate used
 FLAG -  6 chars - Flags are shown according to what your caller did
                    U - Uploaded file
                    D - Downloaded file
                    R - Read messages
                    W - Wrote messages
                    P - Paged Sysop
                    C - Used Cli (You must be maaaaaaaad!!)
 XMOD - 18 chars - Exit method 
 UPLD -  3 chars - How many uploaded files
 DNLD -  3 chars - How many downloaded files
 MESR -  3 chars - How many messages read
 MESW -  3 chars - How many messages written

and here are the colour codes

 1 - White
 2 - Red
 3 - Blue
 4 - Green
 5 - Yellow
 6 - Magenta
 7 - Cyan

Well, I hope all that made sense :) There are a couple of example configs
for you to look at...
 
@{"< >" Link MAIN} Return to the Main Menu
@endnode
@node USAGE "Usage"
---<Using KewlCaller>---

  KewlCaller consists of ONE Main Executable...

  When the Door loads, You will be shown the last ten callers to the BBS!
  Now, Simply press ANY KEY to return to the BBS.












